This paper is about non-autoregressive machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge distillation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve manipulating the complexity of data sets, which could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
